What is Ready Mix Concrete?
Ready mix concrete (RMC) is a factory-prepared concrete mixture composed of cement, aggregates, water, and admixtures, which is batched and mixed at a central plant before being delivered to construction sites in transit mixers. This method eliminates the need for on-site batching, offering numerous advantages such as consistent quality, precise mix proportions, reduced material wastage, and faster project completion. The product is available in various specialized formulations, including standard RMC, high-performance concrete, and self-compacting concrete, to meet diverse construction requirements ranging from residential buildings to large-scale infrastructure projects.
